Zach's Bootcamp
===============
The most common ownership model
Primary software engineer - logging/exports
Primary Data Engineer - Pipeline, Master Data 
Primary Data Analyst/scientist - Metrics/Dashboarfs, Experiments.

What happens when these crossed boundaries persist?
Burnout
Bad team dynamic
The blame game
Bad cross-functional support

Centralized vs Embedded Teams
Centralized : many Data Engineers in one team, knowledge sharing DE's supporting DE's, Prioritization can get complex.
Embedded : Data Engineers in other ebgineering teams, DE gains deep domain knowledge, Islands of responsibility DE's can feel isolated.

Common issues in the pipelines you're bound to face as a Data Engineer

